<br>
The sound of music at one end of the pavilion caught Alexiares's ears.  A grin graced her face, as quickly her feet began to move her over towards the sound.  This was something that she knew and was sure of.  Like the beat of her heart, music was life to Alexiares.  Her palms seem to lift up magically, her wrists twisting them upwards.  Her barefeet began to move across the floor of the pavilion in a light dance.  The little silver bells on her ankles and wrists light sounding as her hips began to sway with her feet's movement.  Her palms upstretched to the Gods, Alexi danced gazing up in praise.  Spinning ever so slightly from time to time, the dancer had a calm relaxed smile. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archeressofdaggerpoint>Archeress of Daggerpoint</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#993300>(5/16/03 1:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Leaving?</span><hr size=1> Tala watched the others quietly for a long time, leaning back against the wall in silent thought. Awhile back she had gone to Sarmatia and had been confronted by the High Priestess of Avalon there. Offered a chance as a priestess, Tala had lept at the opportunity. Now it was only a matter of telling the Vasilissas she'd be going...she didn't want to be concidered a deserter after all. She snapped out of her thoughts and looked around, then took a breath and moved away from the wall, through the crowd and over to Vasilissa Delerium. She saluted her, her gaze flicking over to the man next to her, then back. &quot;Vasilissa...please excuse m'interuption. May I speak wif you m'Queen?&quot; As much 